  <title>The Great Gorilla Jump</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Imagine this: a gorilla, suited up with a parachute, climbs to the top of a tall city building as part of a special wildlife training experiment. 
      After a brief moment of hesitation, the gorilla bravely leaps off the edge. 
      As the parachute deploys and air resistance kicks in, you, as one of the researchers on the ground, begin recording data to study how the gorilla's velocity changes over time.
      Using high-speed sensors, the team records the gorillaâ€™s downward velocity every half-second as it falls. 
      Note that the gorilla touched the ground just after 5 seconds. 
