  <exercises>
  <title>Part (a): How far did the gorilla travel? </title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Recall we can find the distance by <alert>multiplying</alert> the elapsed time and the velocity during the time. 
        The formula is 
        <me>
            \text{distance} = \text{time}\times\text{velocity}
        </me>
        We are given a bunch of data points so let's find the total distance traveled as follows: 
      </p>

      <p>
        (1) Approximate how far the gorilla fell during each half-second interval and fill in the table below. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <table>
            <tabular halign="center" frame="all" rules="all">
                <row header="yes" bottom="medium" >
                <cell>Time (in seconds)</cell>
                <cell>Approximate distance traveled (in feet)</cell>
                </row>
                            
                <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>0 -- 0.5</cell>
                <cell></cell>
                </row>
                            
                <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>0.5 -- 1.0</cell>
                <cell></cell>
                </row>
                            
                <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>1.0 -- 1.5</cell>
                <cell></cell>
                </row>
                            
                <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>1.5 -- 2.0</cell>
                <cell></cell>
                </row>

                <row bottom="minor">
                <cell>2.0 -- 2.5</cell>
